commit.message:
Add CI test to build a Debian package

This test will generate a Debian package and run lintian. The main goals are
test if the program builds to produce a package and generate lintian reports to
find issues.

The final structure is:
    * 05_debian-build.yml: the CI test.
    * debian/: the directory with Debian rules to package. Note that it is a
               packaging a bit less complex, not the same from Debian, but
               is very similar.
    * lintianrc: some lines to configure lintian.
    * run_debian: file with a line to manually enable/disable this test.

There are two important results:
    * lintian_summarized: click to see an abstract about each lintian.
    * lintian_explained: click to see each lintian explained.

Note this packaging will need periodic updates.

commit.message:
Add a CI test for GitHub

It will run after each push to test an initial build, install and uninstall.
After this, a distclean and a second build and install will run to test if
these actions execute twice. Any error in source code will break the build
and invalidate the CI test.
